text.tspan: Global temperature anomalies by El Niño and La Niña conditions
The difference between a month's average land-sea surface temperature and the 1991–2020 average,
measured in degrees Celsius. It is classified as El Niño or La Niña based on the Oceanic Niño Index, which
tracks warming or cooling patterns in the central Pacific Ocean.
Data source: Contains modified Copernicus Climate Change Service information (2025); NOAA National Centers for Environmental
